Went to eat at Siri for the first time as I have heard some fabulous talk about it in the city. The lunch items on the menu were flavorful and stunning. As a food enthusiast, I've been to multiple restaurants representing a wide variety of ethnic food (Thai, Nepali, Korean, Middle Eastern etc...) and would highly recommend this South Indian restaurant for anyone who is on the lookout for authentic Asian food.. The staff and service were very polite and respectful as well. I am certain that I will come here again to satisfy my cravings.

Okay I’m a HUGE foodie and now vegetarian/vegan so finding awesome veggie food options is great! This is the first time I ate here for the first time and will definitely be coming back again! This has become one of my favorite places and top Indian restaurants in the city or suburbs where I live. I’ll come to the city to eat here. So the vegetable springs rolls were piping hot and perfectly crispy with really delicious sweet and spicy sauce but I also ordered some sriracha to make even more spicy and the filling inside was delicious. The paneer dosa and masala dosa were stuffed perfectly and the sambar and chutneys especially the chutneys were delicious. Then had paneer tikka and that was one of the best I can remember if not the best. Highly recommend ordering that. Ordered channa masala with garlic naan and that was good but not I prefer more spicy. I’d give all the other dishes 5/5 but this one and the channa masala more like 4/5 but that’s because I like real spicy but my Mom said it was perfectly made. I look forward to coming back and having more Indo Chinese dishes (fusion Indian).

Also one of the waiters himself told me they don't even let them take the tips which made me feel really bad  There are way better places than this, where u will get good quality indian food and honestly most of the 5 star reviews on here aren't not even authentic

I wish I could give this restaurant more than 5 stars!!! Seriously!!! I came across this place recently and fell in love with their food. So I decided to use them for catering for a socially distanced group lunch at work that we organized outdoors. I had the entire team choose their orders in advanced and placed the order the morning of the event. Unfortunately, the restaurant had a flooring emergency in the kitchen the night before and the kitchen was unexpectedly closed for repair work. I totally panicked: here I was a couple of hours prior to my event with no food... I talked to the owner and explained the situation. He was amazingly accommodating and understanding. In spite of him dealing with an emergency for his business, he decided to honor the order due to my circumstances and open up the kitchen just for that. He went the extra mile, prepared yummylicious food and even delivered it himself although I was more than willing to pick it up. He even went out of his way to make and extra stop in order to provide plastic ware and plates prior to the delivery. But here is the most unusual part: because of his own emergency, the owner was not even ready to accept payments. So he dropped off a ton of food with me and simply told me that I should contact him for the payment the next day, once the restaurant officially reopened. I wish there were more businesses like this out there, that cared so much about their customers and had such a level of trust!!! Needless to say that my work event was a success and everybody LOVED the food!!! Thank you so much Siri Restaurant, you are the best!!!

Chicken Special Kebab  𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐌𝐞𝐚𝐥 What we had was a platter of different styles of chicken cooked in a tandoor: 👉Tandoori chicken – Chicken with bone marinated in yogurt, dry spices, ginger and garlic, and roasted to perfection 👉Chicken Tikka – Boneless chicken breast pieces marinated in yogurt, garlic and dry spices 👉Chicken Reshmi Tikka – Boneless chicken breast pieces marinated in a creamy spicy marinade 👉Chicken Seekh kebab – Ground chicken flavored with fresh herbs and spices skewered and cooked to tenderness.  All of these were just brilliant. Perfectly done, very flavorful, and aromatic. The chicken was spicy, juicy and tender; nothing to complain about. As for the restaurant - the interiors are pretty basic, not much seating space, the staff is nice, and most of what we had was really good, just a little expensive. Buffet might be a bang for your buck. .

Probably the best authentic Indian restaurant in the city. Although I have only had the buffet here One time only, I am very surprised at the quality and authenticity of this place. Plus I have only had their vegetarian selection.  With those caveats out of the way; I am willing to bet that I will be going only to this place and Egg-o-holic from now on. Both of the North Indian and South Indian items tasted wonderful. The sambar, rasam, Mango Dal, curd rice along with the northern style Paneer makhani, mushroom Curry, biryani, naan, Mango kulfi were all delectable.  I have a feeling the meat items are also done well. For a restaurant in the UIC area, I was not expecting this selections and quality. Bravo.  Edited to add: I have been here multiple times since. The weekend buffet has a small selection, but everything is tasty and pretty authentically cooked. Especially the biryani. The dinner menu has a good South Indian selection along with the usual mughlai/Panjabi stuff. I really think this is the best Indian place in the city. You have to get to the burbs to get this quality. They also do a all you can eat Dosa night on Tuesday and a Chaat night on Thursday. Both are worth it. As you can tell, I am really excited to have this kind of place close to go regularly. 👌👍

So... my second job is driving for delivery firm.   When the person place the order they requested plates and plastic ware. I picked up the order, not knowing two plates and plastic ware were requested as I received this through the app, then I deliver the order to a OBGYN at Cook County Stroger Hospital. The doctor went into the hospital after having been given her delivery, she turned around and came back out and asked where the plates and plastic ware were. I told her that I did not know about this oh, and I asked her if she needed me to go get her some plastic ware. She said no, then a security guard told her that she could go into another room right on the main floor and get plates and plastic ware. I called the restaurant immediately after this and told them that the customer, who is the doctor, stated that they put specific notes in the order about plates and plastic ware. It is upon information and belief vet in Pryor postings of reviews for this restaurant there are a few different customers mentioning the lack of plates and plastic ware. This leads me to believe that these owners really don't care whether or not you get plates or plastic ware. Therefore, if you are ordering from this place and, you require plates and plastic ware, you better let him know up front, you better put it in bold Capitals in any online ordering mechanism, and it might be a good idea to follow up with a little phone call so these people truly understand what you mean when you put those notes in the applications. I gave them a 5-star review because I don't believe in shooting at people like that I am just going to give them this constructive criticism perhaps they will stop trying to save pennies.
